title: For Sale:  Rare Zastava M92 Krinkov AK-47 Pistol
postcontent:
Where to start?  Do the research on YouTube and you'll find that this is one of the finest, most well made examples of an AK anywhere in the world.  The dust cover is hinged and this pistol version is just begging to be SBR'd.
I hand stained and polished the wood and added a really sweet Magpul AFG angled foregrip, which isn't a true vertical foregrip by ATF standards so it's compliant, yet gives great control when firing this rig.
I also added a CAA ergo grip which reduces felt recoil and a shorty picatinny rail on top which still allows the factory iron sights to be used and looks great with the included Bushnell red dot sight.
This Zastava is a 7.62x39mm fire breather and the muzzle fire will extend several feet out and attracts a lot of attention at the range when shooting commando style.  I've put around 300 rounds through it and it's never jammed or had a single malfunction even once.  It will eat whatever you put in it including cheap TulAmmo...it's not picky at all and is so much fun to shoot.  I can easily hit a 6 inch metal target at 100 yards using the factory sights and they have a single flip adjustment out to 200 yards.
The factory 30 round metal magazine allows the bolt to stay open after the last round.  Everything is so precise on this gun and the trigger is better than my AR-10.
I have my CFP and prefer those with the same.  Buyer must be at least 18 and have a valid drivers license and be able to legally own and operate a firearm.

title: For Sale:  1929 Lefever 16ga Nitro Special, 28"bbl, Full/Mod
postcontent:
This is a 1929 Lefever 16ga Nitro Special, 28"bbl, Full/Mod chokes.  The American Lefever Nitro Special was introduced in 1921 and discontinued in 1948.  It was not a true Dan Lefever design; rather it was an Ithaca boxlock design, the precursor of the famous Ithaca NID that appeared four years later. Ithaca had bought Lefever in 1916 and wanted to capitalize on the famous name. The earlier Lefever double guns manufactured by the Lefever Arms Company and D.M. Lefever and Sons were highly regarded and are mostly collectors' items today. 

The Nitro Special was not a fancy gun, but it was hell for strong. Nitro Specials were designed for modern smokeless powder shells (but not steel shot) and any Nitro Special that has not been abused should be safe to use today, which is why the model is included here. 

Most Nitro Specials have color case hardened receivers, double triggers, plain extractors, a low solid rib, and semi-pistol grip walnut stocks and splinter forearms checkered about 16 lpi. However, there were variations, including beavertail forearms and a single selective trigger. Gauges were 12, 16, 20, and .410 bore.   Item G-34389-1

We have additional higher resolution pictures of this item available upon request.

Call REDACTED or come by Green Country Arms & Pawn in Tulsa, OK, (9075 E 31st St, Tulsa, OK). Be sure to mention that you saw our ad on Armslist.

We can also ship to a FFL dealer. Shipping is $20 for all hand guns and $40 for long guns in the lower 48 states. We do NOT ship to CA. We will ship to NY, CO, CT or any other state within the restrictions of those states. If you have a question, please ask. Payment can be made using a credit card (NO Am. Ex.), by phone or with postal money order (upon clearing). We are currently not accepting personal checks. 

You can also come check out our guns, ammo and accessories in person at our store M-F 9am - 6pm, Sat 10am - 5pm. We're closed on Sundays.
